I have more sets of headphones/earbuds than I care to admit, but I somehow manage to talk myself into buying another pair every so often. With these, the excuse I made for myself was that I didn\'t have a decent pair of Bluetooth earbuds. I had a set of cheap BT earbuds that I picked up from a local convenience store a couple years ago, but I never really liked them that much and so rarely used them, which meant the battery was always dead whenever I did need them. By the time the battery was done charging, I didn\'t need to use them anymore, so they would sit on the shelf for a month until I needed them again, at which point the battery was dead again, and so on...  I thought maybe if I had a decent pair that I liked better, I would actually use them more often and wouldn\'t run into that same cycle of frustration. I was thinking about getting a pair of premium buds that everyone seems to have these days, but was hesitant to drop ~$200 on something that could still wind up sitting in a drawer 95% of the time. I stumbled onto these and thought the $20 price tag seemed perfect, especially seeing as Soundcore is a division of/owned by Anker. I love Anker\'s products, so I figured these would be good quality, so I could see how they work out and decide if I wanted to spring for a more expensive upgrade later on (or if my aversion is just to wireless buds in general and save myself $180).  Well, I\'ve had these for a couple months now and they ended up being even better than I expected. I\'m sure better quality could be had, but it\'s hard to beat the value you get with these. They sound great, connect easily, and stay in my ears (for the most part). I don\'t use them every day, but that\'s mainly because I have a wife and young kids that are frequently trying to get my attention, and these block too much external sound to hear them well (hitting pause and asking "What did you say?" every 10 seconds is more frustration for everybody than it\'s worth, haha). Just using one earbud works as a workaround, but still, I\'d prefer to have music in both ears if I can.  Side story  I know it\'s stupid, but I have a weird habit of squirrelling away expensive stuff. Instead, I am naturally inclined to use a cheaper, notsonice variant in my regular routine, I guess in a backwards way of trying to keep my nice things nice. These earbuds are such good quality that I find myself wanting to "save" them and keep them hidden away. Moral of the story, the quality definitely seems like a notch above my expectations for this price point, which is a great thing!  If you\'re looking for a decent pair of wireless earbuds that won\'t break the bank, these are an excellent option. I am very pleased with my purchase  it was well worth it! Audio App. It\'s basically a music player designed to detect the sony earphones. If you use spotify you can use this app to setup an equaliser. It plays MP3 from your storage too. Nel mondo degli auricolari true wireless, la competizione è feroce. Le Huawei FreeBuds 6i emergono come una proposta interessante grazie alla cancellazione attiva del rumore, compatibilità con iOS e Android, e bassi potenti. Ma riescono a soddisfare le aspettative? Esaminiamole nel dettaglio.  Descrizione del Prodotto:  Le Huawei FreeBuds 6i sono auricolari true wireless con cancellazione attiva del rumore 3.0, Bluetooth 5.3 e possibilità di connessione a doppio dispositivo. La durata della batteria arriva fino a 35 ore utilizzando la custodia di ricarica. Sono disponibili nel colore bianco, progettati per offrire un\'esperienza audio bilanciata con enfasi sui bassi.  Unboxing:  La confezione include gli auricolari, una custodia di ricarica, un cavo USBC, gommini di diverse misure e un manuale d\'uso. Il packaging è semplice ma funzionale, con ogni componente al suo posto.  Esperienza d\'Uso:  Gli auricolari risultano confortevoli grazie ai gommini intercambiabili. La connessione Bluetooth è rapida e affidabile, e la funzione di connessione a due dispositivi si rivela utile per chi utilizza più dispositivi contemporaneamente. La cancellazione attiva del rumore è efficace nel ridurre i suoni ambientali, migliorando l\'immersione nell\'ascolto.  Prestazioni:  Le FreeBuds 6i offrono un audio bilanciato con bassi profondi. Sebbene il volume massimo non sia molto elevato, la qualità audio rimane buona per la fascia di prezzo. La batteria è un punto di forza, con una lunga durata e una ricarica rapida che offre ore di utilizzo con pochi minuti di ricarica.  Pro:  Efficace cancellazione del rumore Audio bilanciato con bassi potenti Connessione Bluetooth 5.3 stabile Possibilità di connessione a doppio dispositivo Lunga durata della batteria e ricarica rapida  Contro:  Volume massimo non elevato Design standard Limitata distinzione dai concorrenti nella stessa fascia di prezzo  Critiche e Limitazioni:  Il volume massimo potrebbe non soddisfare gli utenti che preferiscono un ascolto a livelli molto alti. Il design non offre particolari innovazioni, rendendo difficile distinguere questo modello dai concorrenti. Tuttavia, per il prezzo, le funzionalità offerte sono di buon livello.  Conclusioni:  Le Huawei FreeBuds 6i rappresentano una scelta solida per chi cerca auricolari wireless con buona cancellazione del rumore, qualità audio decente e lunga durata della batteria a un prezzo accessibile. Nonostante alcuni limiti, offrono un eccellente rapporto qualitàprezzo.  Spero che questa recensione vi abbia aiutato a scegliere. Se così fosse, vi sarei grato se cliccaste sul tasto "utile" 😀  Grazie, Andrea Read more']

Read more', 'I am almost 65 years old SO, I DO NOT have the ears of a 18 year old. That said, I consider these to be good for these reasons:  A: Exceptional battery life.  B: Call quality that was considered good UNTIL I did a direct comparison to my Blueparrott B450XT’s  NO WHERE NEAR the quality of the Blue 450’s, BUT the Blues are made specifically for calls in noisey environments. . Blues are in my opionion the defacto standard by which all other ANC phone calls should be judged. My "demo" for people is to run my upright vacuum cleaner whilst on a call. People on the other end cannot hear it AT ALL – REALLY!, I hear them, and they hear me perfectly! TRULY amazing! I did the same test with these and alas they failed miserably in comparison. I expected that. I was told they sound like I am in a room away from the microphone, a bit fishtank like, and muddy. SO, they’ll do in a call but not as a primary phone call device in noise. Yup, they drown out all the extraneous noises like people talking, Air conditioners, fans, Water coolers, hums, etc. ALL gone with nothing playing through them!  I bought them primarily for playing on my PS5, and watching TV late at night. They do both quite well.  D: Amazingly, my ears do not sweat much in these even after prolonged use. I’ve ordered those Dekoni Suede Earpads for them as well just for added comfort. (https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BS4T3X62?psc=1&ref=ppx_yo2ov_dt_b_product_details) (5/16/23  Returned The earpads: they claim they are suede when in fact they are 2/3 suede. E: They are longterm comfortable unless you have ears like a B52 in which case you will probably be stuffing bits.  As for music, I find them to be more flat without pronounced highs or bass  which I prefer. The EQ on the app is a nice feature. Again, I remind you, I’m not 18. ;)  Pricewise, they ARE a bit expensive but the build quality seems better than most.  If you have the time, I would HIGHLY recommend you test several brands and models at a store simply because sound quality is subjective and EVERYONE has their preference. UPDATE: 5/23/23  Returning (REPLACING) Headphones  Why? They started acting "Funky". UPDATE 6323: New pair are working as they should no connection issues or on/off bttun problems. UPDATE 21624: Still working perfectly and I use them nearly every night to sleep. Achei as almofadas muito boas e confortáveis, ele não tem um isolamento de ruídos perfeito, mas é bem decente, o formato dele impede que fique apertado na cabeça (é isso que afeta o isolamento), o que é muito bom quando se usa por várias horas seguidas, não senti que as almofadas esquentaram tanto, mas deu uma incomodada em certo momento (levando em consideração que moro no norte do país e a média aqui é 37°C). Vi algumas pessoas reclamando do volume, eu achei bom, não vai fazer maravilhas se alguém estiver falando muito perto, mas é o suficiente pra andar na rua sem ouvir nada ou ir à academia em horário de pico. O formato dele me incomodou um pouco, sei que faz parte da identidade visual, mas essa aparência mais quadrada me dá a impressão de deixar a pessoa mais cabeçuda kkkkk. A embalagem dele é ótima, ele vem dentro de uma sacola protetora que é muito boa pra transportálo caso você não tenha uma case, a caixa do produto é bem compacta, o que agrada bastante pois é fácil de guardar. Recomendo que peçam pra ser enviado na embalagem da Amazon, é muito mais seguro, visto que a embalagem dele é bem chamativa. A entrega foi bem rápida, 2 semanas somente (a previsão era de 2 meses). Gostei bastante do aplicativo, ele é fácil, simples, bem direto e funcionou imediatamente. Adorei a função de rastreamento dele (através do Google, não sei tem pra iOS), nem sabia que ele tinha isso, mas gostei muito. Outra boa surpresa foi o microfone, funciona MUITO bem pra gravar áudio e o som não tem granulação, fica perfeito, pra realizar chamadas também é muito prático. É um fone bastante conveniente e compacto, ideal pra usar no dia a dia, não sei se é o melhor pra atividades de impacto (como corrida ou crossfit), pois não testei. All Reviews: ['سماعه ديه ملهاش حل في الدنيا تحفه بمعنه الكلمه جمدا جدا الف شكر امازون بس السعر كتير جدا بس حلو اوي', 'السماعات بتفصل كل شويه وانا بسمع اغانيه وشويه تشتغل واحده وتفصل التانيه', 'After 4 months of use ,left side not working', 'ممتازة لكن تصميمها مش كويس فقدت السماعة اليمين من غير ما احس', 'Estou usando o fone intraauricular da Sony há quase três semanas e estou impressionado! O controle de ruído e a qualidade do microfone são excelentes, especialmente quando comparados a outros fones da mesma categoria. A durabilidade da bateria também me surpreendeu, durando mais de 8 horas sem recarga.  Tenho outros modelos de concorrentes famosos, mas este se destaca em cancelamento de ruído e duração da bateria. Na categoria intraauricular, poucos modelos oferecem uma qualidade de microfone decente. Eu daria uma nota entre 7 e 8 para o microfone, o que é ótimo para um fone desse tipo. Para qualidade de microfone excepcional, geralmente é necessário um modelo que cubra toda a orelha.  Um ponto negativo é que o manual veio em japonês, mas encontrei facilmente uma versão em inglês na internet. Isso não desqualifica o fone, apenas um detalhe a considerar.  Outro ponto positivo é a sincronização com diversos dispositivos de diferentes marcas. Alternar entre dispositivos Apple e Android é fácil, algo que não vi em outros modelos.  Estou confortável em dar a nota máxima: 5 estrelas. Read more', 'There’s a bit of possible Sony hate going on in some reviews, like others I got burned on a pair of WF10004XM refurbished and one of the batteries started failing after a year. Wasn’t worth the cost of repair. Have others from QCY and Soundcore that were surprisingly good for less cost. Also had trouble with refurbished headphones WH1000XM4, luckily had added insurance. Cut to buying a new pair that have been flawless. Got the Sony WFC700N a couple months ago to scratch my earbud itch. Very good for the price. If you’re not ready to throw down $300 for the XM5 they’re a great alternative. Not quite as musical, but no gripes anyway. You can get picky about the throwback buttons but oh well. One comment before I get more specific on the XM5. I fully agree with another review that calls out Sony for how complicated their Sony Connect app has become. It could be simplified for people who don’t want to get into the tech so much. Now, how do they sound? I’m impressed and I’m not using them to their full potential. Using with iPhone so Bluetooth SBC codec is the most basic and lowest quality solution (after digging into the codec question a bit more it does appear that the iPhone has the AAC codec also). However, with the help of Sony’s equalizer and DSEE function I’m very happy with the sound. I almost don’t want to try them with a better codec and then have to go back. (Still applies with AAC, DSE does improve sound) I need treble boost for my old ears and having played bass no surprise I like a lot of bass. These don’t disappoint. I did an AB comparison with the XM4 headphones and they didn’t have quite the low end but good and punchy with good definition between bass and drums.both can become nice and “growly” on the low end. Noise cancellation is very good, not as good as the headphones but after only a couple days I have been quite satisfied so far. Comfort level is better than the XM4 buds, but I’m so pissed I wasted the money now I don’t want to dig them out to compare audio! I think Sony really improved the fit and design to be lighter, more comfortable, and have impressive sound. Let’s just hope they found a better battery. Used overnight and had battery left in the morning but playing audiobook on timer so i couldn’t say how long continuous playback. I’ll update after I’ve had them longer. (Update) battery life seems to be very similar to the XM4. Sometimes I have battery left in the morning sometimes it comes up short. Another follow up, comes with 4 sets of tips but apparently I have very large ear canals as I’m unable to get a complete seal with the included buds. The large felt good at first but when I used the connect app to check for airtight seals I could not get them to seal. Fortunately I have many tips I’ve saved over the years and by mixing, matching, and testing I have a couple that seal. I even tried ordering extra large tips from a couple vendors and they didn’t work either. Nice that Sony is including extra small but what about us with extra large needs! I do have a possible solution on the way, find a video on YouTube that shows how to use Sugro glue rolled up and inserted in the mushroom part of the tip. Press in the ear to get a fit and then allow to cure over night. Hoping it works, I have a few tips I’d like to try this on. Was even investigating custom molded tips but for $150 plus I’ll try the Sugro hack… 8/5/23 tried the Sugro hack yesterday. Still have to work to get an airtight fit but it definitely helped. My opinion on the sound has not diminished. Excellent with what I listen too. A lot of classic rock but also new material from Elle King and others. Listening to Lourdes “Royals” a very deep bass which presents low, solid, and clear. You can easily distinguish the bass and drums. The low rumbling bass of Pink Floyd “Welcome to the Machine” couldn’t be much better in any buds. Almost like I could feel it. I’m now using the WFC700n as my workout and dog walking buds. Sound signature is very similar but the bass is not quite as good. One thing they are lacking is the airtight fit check in the app. I had to use other tips and the Sugro mold hack to get a good consistent fit in both. The included tips are worthless to me and my big ears. I see a lot of criticism of the noise cancellation for the XM5. I have no way to measure so it’s pretty subjective but I’m not disappointed. At least as good as the XM4. But with any ANC earbuds the airtight seal is critical. If you’re not ready to throw down $300 the WFC700n are a very good alternative, but are not touch controlled, a single button on each side. Not quite as good on the low end but not disappointing either. In direct comparison you can hear the difference. I still think these are 5 star worthy. I’d take off half a star because of the somewhat complex app but if you like to tinker with the sound and features, give it back. People who are not “technical minded” may find it intimidating. I find it useful but jammed with some features I wouldn’t normally use, like automatically changing settings depending on location as an example. Some might find it useful but not me. The equalizer and clear bass functions are excellent. DSEE function makes a noticeable difference in sound quality. Happier with these than I was with the XM4. Just hope the batteries last, I would hope Sony changed from the $70 replacement cost batteries (not including labor) used in the XM4 as apparently so many people had problems with them dying out after a few months. 9/22/23 Used these today instead of the WFC700n for my indoor cycling and to walk the dog. Usually I do those activities with the cheaper buds as for $300 I want to take every precaution to protect them. So…more feedback on the ANC. Definitely a difference on the bike with 2 pretty loud blower fans on. The WFC700n does a very good job in the same situation but I could definitely tell a difference. Could hardly hear the fans at all and the WF1000XM5 does have the superior sound performance. Note these blowers are loud enough that if I have my Apple Watch to close to them I get the over 90db warning. They’re not 90db from the bike but they are loud. These cancelled almost all the noise. With volume on my music I don’t hear the fans at all. Read more', "Best ear pods, no lag, adjustable equalizer via app, excellent noise cancellation. Amazing Base. Build quality is superb. Fits very well in ear. Excellent battery life. Have used Bose earpods but I find these better. You can't go wrong with these.", 'سماعة اسطورية، تأتي بأكثر وسادة تلائم حجم الأذنين، اداء الصوت ممتاز، العزل اسطوري جدا ولكن الاكثار من وضع العزل الصوتي قد يسبب صداع، مدة استخدام السماعة طويل ومبهر جدا، وسادة السماعة قد تكون سريعة الاتساخ ولكن جيدة، بعد استخدام السماعة لمدة تتجاوز الشهور بدأ ابقاء السماعه في الآذن يسبب الم في الطبلة، وهذا منطقي بحكم استخدامي المبالغ للسماعة، عموما تستتحق بحق.', 'The sound quality between my AirPods and the Sony WM’s is enormous, the depth of sound on the Sony’s are way beyond the AirPods. Both have connectivity issues, the AirPods being more troublesome when they choose to disconnect. However the AirPods are easier to use and less sensitive and the AirPods are more comfortable over a longer period of use. Final verdict, if audio quality is your priority the Sony option is notably ahead.']

I wanted something more premium feeling and sounding, and as an Android user, I went with the Galaxy Buds2. These kind of let me down a little bit. The sound quality was fantastic, so was the ANC, but the fit was quite poor and they only lasted me a year. Now I only get like 12 hours of battery on the buds and the case needs charging every couple days. I did use them quite a bit, but it does sting that I paid over $200 for them and they only lasted a year.  Then last week I realized I need a new pair. I enjoy the convenience of wireless buds and use them a lot when I am out and about commuting and when trail running. I still have my expensive Headphones for home and office use, but needed something for more casual (ab)use.  So then a quick amazon search showed me these Anker buds. Priced at $35, I instantly ordered them and they arrived a couple days later. So I have now used them for a couple days and I am genuinely very content with these. For less money than the first pair I got in 2019, these sound and feel a lot more premium. The quality is I'd say 85% of the Samsung buds 2, and I never really cared for ANC or transparency mode, so these are great that they don't have any fancy features.  The Good: They sound very decent, cannot really complain for the price. Could easily fool a nonaudiophile that these are highend.  Fit and design are very reasonable for the price. The case feels strong, the buds are light.  Great battery life so far. They came fully charged and after about 68 hours of listening, the app still says the buds have 80% left. This is fantastic.  The app does have some useful features. There are several EQ options, but I prefer the Rock preset the most since that's my jam. Others have complained that the App doesn't have the White Noise feature, but that is not true. It definitely has white noises and this is something I look forward to using some more. Some decent sound options.  Best BANG for your buck!  Some downsides:  The build quality is certainly acceptable, but overall not the most ergonomic. Case is slippery, the lid feels a bit heavy, getting the buds in and out is a little finicky, Buds fit well in my ear but do stick out just a tad more than the galaxy buds. But given the better fit, I'll allow the sticking out.  Overall: Get these if you are like me and use wireless buds for casual listening for more than a few hours a day. Buying premium buds like Airpods or samsung buds seems like a waste because they only last 12 years, and with no righttorepair or the ability to change the batteries, these become a lot more attractive. Read more', 'One of the best products I ever used never had issue with their products, very durable long lasting hours sound quality is astonishing and the finish is amazing.', 'Sound quality  The EQ is fairly flat and accurate to what the listening experience should be. Mids and highs are crystal clear and the bass is not as boosted compare to other headphones I\'ve owned This is something I personally prefer. They are not overhear headphones with large drivers so I\'m comparing them in the same category of headphone.  Comfort  I use these while exercising, I can headbang and not have them fly off my head. I also use them to listen to things while sleeping often with one pressed against the pillow (not smart) but they are comfortable enough to not disturb me. They don\'t have silicone buds so they don\'t irritate my ears, but as a negative there is more sound leakage as a result of this as they don\'t make that perfect seal.  Call quality/Noise cancellation  They handle calls in a datacentre quite well (According to a Google search this can be 96 db of background noise), people I\'m on the phone to don\'t hear a thing. While I\'m being hit by gale force winds, it can sometimes be audible to the person on the other end of the call but this seems to be minor. They work well with Google Hangouts and Teams on my phone or PC. Call audio quality is great and it does a great job at cancelling out any background office noise.  ANC  I did try it out on an aeroplane once but again, the head phones don\'t make a perfect seal. It works well enough but I don\'t like the feeling of ANC and haven\'t heard ANC of other recent headphones to give a good comparison.  Bluetooth  pairing is easy and seamless between two devices. On the rare occasion you\'ll need to "forget device" and repair them. I suspect this is just a Bluetooth issue generally as That seems to happen with all devices every now and then. They pair to my phone and PC laptop and iPad, but only seem to pair to two devices at once. If I connect to my Laptop and Phone, then I\'ll need to hit "connect" in Bluetooth settings on my PC to drop one of the other connections  The battery life  They are advertised to have 5 hours of playback but I seem to get more, maybe this is because I\'m not using ANC and don\'t have them at full volume in the office. In the event they were out of battery while I was jumping onto a call, I\'m able to put them in their case, join onto a call and place one headphone in my ear. The 20s of charge time usually gets me a few minutes of playback. At which point I swap the ear bud just before it runs out of battery, that gets me 10 minutes on the other ear bud. The case gets charged every 34 days.  Build quality  I have "tested" the build quality by dropping them several times, both the case and earbuds "bounce" fairly well. The case has some scuffs but the hinge is solid, the magnet holds the lid closed and magnets also hold the headphones into the charging slots. Overall, can\'t complain. It had a "premium" feel but that soon worn off after it was dropped taking it out of my pocket and then kicked a few meters as I was mid stride. It held up nicely.  Overall, I\'ve owned the headphones for over a year with daily use. They were a little bit more pricey compared to when I bought them and I\'d still consider them great value for money. Read more']

ANC(Cancelamento de ruídos)(8.0)  É bom pela faixa de preço, serve bem para momentos como para assistir vídeos ou só se vc quiser se isolar mesmo, ele funciona e realmente te isola do ambiente, e vai atender a maioria dos usuários. Aperto na cabeça (10) Ele não aperta muito na cabeça, somente o suficiente para o fone se manter preso na cabeça, e isso é fantástico! (na minha opinião) ele é diferente de outros fones concorrentes. Adendos:  1.O fone treme na cabeça (nas frequências graves, quando elas tocam, você consegue ouvir e sentir elas vibrando na cabeça), se você não gosta disso, talvez não queira este fone, (mas é normal para fones desse tamanho isso ocorrer), porém em minha experiência achei isso muito bom, dá uma maior imersão no áudio. 2.Sobre o áudio p2 é bom mas fica com volume ligeiramente inferior ao bluetooth. E infelizmente as funções no modo P2 de noise cancelling, equalizador, dentre outros ficam indisponíveis, uma vez que o fone fica totalmente desligado quando isto é usado. 3. Para realizar chamadas eu gostei bastante do áudio, bem alto e de boa definição( levando em consideração que é um dispositivo bluetooth, ainda é um desafio atrelar qualidade de audio do microfone em uma chamada), sendo excelente para realizar reuniões no zoom, meet e dentre outros programas (como o Discord) 4.Os Codecs desse fone são: SBC, AAC + HD AUDIO( se o aparelho assim suportar) , o que é bom, pois vários fones adotam o SBC nessa faixa de preço, mas isso tem mudado e está virando mais comum ter AAC como codec. o SBC entrega uma qualidade mais mediana , mas que também não é ruim. O JBL Tune 720BT possui um design que ajuda a minimizar os ruídos externos, permitindo uma experiência de áudio mais imersiva e clara, perfeita para quem precisa de concentração ou deseja curtir música sem distrações.  3. **Graves Ótimos**: A qualidade de som dos graves é notável. Alguns usuários podem sentir que o fone de ouvido não atinge volumes muito altos, o que pode ser um problema para aqueles que gostam de ouvir música em níveis mais elevados.  2. **Vazamento de Som no Volume Máximo**: Além disso, ao aumentar o volume para o máximo, o som pode ser ouvido por pessoas ao redor. Isso pode ser inconveniente em ambientes silenciosos ou quando se busca privacidade, já que outras pessoas podem acabar ouvindo a música que você está escutando.  ### Conclusão  O JBL Tune 720BT é uma excelente escolha para quem procura um fone de ouvido com longa duração de bateria, bom isolamento de ruídos e graves de alta qualidade. Die stehen den Platzhirschen in nichts nach und kosten wesentlich weniger 🤷\u200d♂️ eine echte Kaufempfehlung von daher 5 Sterne', "First of all before I get started, I am not an audiophile and I bought these with my own money, it's an honest buyers review, I'm just your average bloke who likes a bit of tech, appreciates good sound, listening to music, podcasts and audiobooks on my 1hr + train commute.  I pre ordered these 6i freebuds and they arrived the day after the their release date.  Why did I order them? Purely because my dog decided to chew up one of my 5i Freebuds!!  Packaging  I'm not someone who needs a nice flashy cardboard box when it comes to buying anything. As long as the product is well protected then I'm good.  As usual though Huawei again use a good thick cardboard box and inner card linings/tray with the buds nicely protect in an opaque plastic sleeve. Remove the earbuds cardboard and you'll find the charge lead, a choice of different sized silcone tips and your usual paperwork. All very well made and presented.  Case & Buds Build quality  Again Huawei have come through here with top marks. The case & buds have a gloss finish which punch above their weight at this price point. The case just feels nice in your hand, very much like a worn smooth pebble. Being this shape means it very easily slips into your jeans or trouser pocket unlike many bud cases I've owned.  As mentioned before, the gloss finish is also applied to the earbuds, again giving a premium feel. The case has your usual led to show its charging and a USB  C port, there is no wireless charging feature which some will find annoying, personally I'm fine with plugging them in.  Connectivity  I have an android phone so can't speak for Iphone users here. I already had the AI life app from Huawei, you can't get it on Google play store but it's easy enough to get from Huawei and I highly recommend using it.  Once you open up the app you can follow the instructions and your earbuds easily pair. There are plenty of options for sound, ANC and even a find earbuds feature which is a nice touch.  Earbuds in action  Over the last couple of years I have bought too many earbuds than I should, trying to find what is right for me. From £25 soundpeats to £200 XM4 Sonys. My happy place was the 5i Freebuds ( until their untimely demise).  The things that are important to me are decent, sound, effective ANC and easy to use controls.  Sound As I said I'm definitely am not an audiophile but I appreciate good quality. The 6i's I believe are about as good as you get at this price point . Some reviews of the 5i and 6i have said that for music they can sound 'flat' and I can see where they are coming from but personally I like them, you can fiddle with the settings and in my humble opinion I the clarity of highs is about right, the bass is clear and not muddled, if you're a bass junky they aren't for you but listening to different styles of music I think Huawei have covered pretty well. I would like them to be louder but that may be down to euro laws I've been told.  ANC  in the app you can set the ANC manually or it can be switched to an auto mode which adapts to your surroundings. Personally I have it manually adjusted to ultra, the highest setting. I have ANC on to drown out idiots who make calls on their phone speaker or just generally irratate me on the train  of which there are many. On Ultra the ANC is very good, I'd say the best you will get with this style of earbuds definitely better than the Sony XM4's I had which are highly rated by many. They won't silence everything but you can easily listen to a podcast or audio book without getting distracted by people or background noise. Huawei have done a great job here.  Controls the controls are customisable in the app. There is a swipe up/ swipe down on the stalks for volume. The next/previous track, pause/play, answer/hang are all controlled by a light tap or three on the top of each bud, again all can be changed to your personal preference in the app. The sensitivity is spot on, not too sensitive which can be a pain on some earbuds. The earbuds also pause when removed, a feature I didn't think I would be bothered about until I first used it on the Sony XM4'S, it's just very handy to have.  Comfort  The 6i's are very light and ergonomics are great, you literally don't know you have them in.  Comparisons. I said that I have had a few earbuds they inclue the Sony XM4'S, Sound peats tru air 2+, Anker P40i, Cambridge ( can't remember model, Panasonic RZS500WEK and Huawei Freebuds 5i. Oveall for value, performance and quality I would put the 6i's at the top, no they don't sound as good as the Sonys but they are under half the price and I had issues with two pairs of XM4's which resulted in a refund and Somy weren't helpful. The soundpeats whilst good value are nowhere near in the same league sound wise.  The Ankers? Very good for the money but missing a few features of the 6i's.  When it comes to comparing the 5i's its not so easy. They are an improvement ( call quality is meant be better which I haven't really tested tbh) The photos i have uploaded show the white 6i's and black 5i for comparison. Whilst the cases are near identical they aren't interchangeable.  Sound wise they are very similar, the 6i's do have the edge.  As you can see in thr photos there physically is hardly any difference.  So, if you put them side by side? I'd take the 6i's definitely.  Would I upgrade just because they are the new model? That's a no from me, the 5i's are very close in every way, there isn't enough improvement to upgrade for the sake of it from where I stand.  So overal as you have probably worked out, I think Huawei have done a top job and they should be right up there if you're in the market for a new set of earbuds mid price upwards.  Enjoy your music 👍 Read more"]

Names: Soundcore by Anker Life P3i Hybrid Active Noise Cancelling Earbuds, 4 Mics, AI-Enhanced Calls, 10mm Drivers, Powerful Sound, App for Custom EQ, 36H Playtime, Fast Charging, Transparency, Bluetooth 5.2
descriptions: (Brand : Name soundcore)   (Color : Off-White)   (Headphones : Jack 3.5 mm Jack)   (Noise : Control Active Noise Cancellation)   (Sensitivity : 45 dB)
About Phone: Incredible Sound Loved by 20 Million People, AI-Enhanced Clear Calls: Get clear calls anywhere you go with 6 dedicated microphones built into the wireless earbuds and a noise-isolating AI algorithm that picks up your voice precisely.
All Reviews: ['Excellent product, noise cancellation great, sound good in voice and music, acceptable battery life', 'السماعة ليست أصلية...والوكيل في مصر... عندما توجهت إلية...أفاد بعدم تقديم ضمان على المنتج', 'مش بنصح حد يشتريه المنتج مش بيوصل اصلا', "Full disclosure, given the price, I wasn't expecting much from these headphones, but these have surpassed my expectations. I have an iPhone 14 Pro Max with AirPods Pro 2; I wanted a pair of less expensive backup wireless buds for use in our sauna and other situations where I wouldn't mind losing or damaging these, but I want to protect my $300 Apple AirPods.  The entire experience of unboxing, pairing and setup is topnotch. Downloading their app, which walks you through pairing, took less than a minute, and the earphones came fully charged. The earphones and the charging case are made from quality materials; the fit and finish are excellent. They're not as substantial feeling as AirPods Pro 2, but they're also 1/6th the cost; keep that in mind.  The case has a nice clicky magnetic closure and a USBC charging port. There's a USBC to USBC cable in the box. The case doesn't support wireless charging. Charing the case is easy; there's an LED on the front, flashing when charging and solid when charged.  When removed from the case, the earphones themselves automatically turn on and connect to the paired device seamlessly. I left them on the default EQ; it sounds good as is. The notice cancellation has three modes, active, transparency and off. Coming from using Samsung and Apple headphones with ANC, these are 80% of what Apple delivers. With ANC on, they do a great job at cancelling most of the ambient noise but are not quite as good as Apple AirPods Pro 2 or Samsung Galaxy Buds Pro. Again, remember the cost and value they represent. To even have ANC at this price point is more than I expected. The music sounds fantastic; I listened to some acoustic songs, and the voices and instruments are clear, even at max volume. The silicone ear tips are comfortable and contribute to the notice cancellation. Make sure you have a snug fit for ANC to work; there are differentsized ear tips in the box. Comfort is 9/10; no difference between these and the Apple AirPods Pro 2.  I made a few calls and used these on some Zoom calls; they sound great. Voices are clear, and I asked the others on the call; they could hear me perfectly well; the four mics do a great job here.  Putting the price aside, I'd say these are 85% of what the Apple AirPods 2 Pro are, but considering the price, they represent the best value on the market IMO. They're 1/6th the cost, and while not perfect, they do everything very well with no drama. I can't comment on the longterm durability or battery life, but I'll come to edit the review in 6 months and one year to comment on this.  Anker has come a long way here, these are awesome, and I'd highly recommend them. Read more", "I had the latest model of ear buds from a certain company named after a fruit that I spend $250 on. Unfortunately they got stolen and I bought these until I could save up enough to buy better quality earbuds again. Looks like I won't need to upgrade!  Pros:  The sound quality is insane! I have no idea how it sounds so good at this price point. Not quite as good as the top of the line but way better than mid to uppermid range buds.  Transparency mode is incredible! No drop in sound quality, no extra noise added, the pass through audio isn't too tinny. I have no clue how Anker could figure this out in an earbuf under $100 while others couldn't get that right for $250.  Button customization! You can change what the buttons do in the app! And there's 3 different button commands per ear!  Comfy! I don't even feel them in my ear, it's crazy how nice they feel, idk if it's just my ear shape but usually earbuds hurt my ears after a couple of hours  Bluetooth is working amazingly. No connecting while it's in the case which was a huge problem with my last earbuds  Cons:  ANC is weaker than competitors, but not bad. It will definitely help on an airplane or around constant sources of noise, but someone talking around you is going to be just as audible as in normal mode. That said, the passive noise cancelation is pretty good so I don't even feel like I'll need the ANC except in certain scenarios.  Button placement. To press the button you have to push it into your ear which is a little uncomfortable. I wish they had put the button on the side of the stems. Luckily they don't require much pressure so it's not a huge deal, and it's better than having to tap on them like some ear buds.  Case is pretty cheap, I don't feel like it would hold up well if dropped.  Meh:  Battery life is almost as advertised on normal mode. Charges relatively quickly. No complaints. Compré estos junto a los Jabra Elite 75 active y, aunque ambos tienen una calidad excepcional, los Jbl vencen en algunos aspectos clave.  La batería, es inaudito lo que llega a durar, junto con su caja, llevo más de 3 semanas viajando, yendo al gimnasio... A toda potencia, y aún le queda la mitad de la carga... Debe de ser magia negra o no lo entiendo.  Sonido rico, potente y unos graves simplente brutales, ideales para el tipo de música que escucho (rock, metal...).  La app una maravilla, la mejor que he probado para adaptar el sonido a tus preferencias, muy por encima de Jabra.  Y lo más importante para mí... NO SE CAEN, puedo estar en el gym sudando como un pollo y ahí se quedan, no se resbalan ni hacen el amago de ir a hacerlo, por lo que se mantiene el "vacío" y por lo tanto no pierde potencia el sonido, como sí sucede con los Jabra 75, Galaxy Buds y tantos otros. Por el aspecto parece que sean pesados e incómodos, pero nada más lejos de la realidad, su forma tiene más sentido de la que aparenta a primera vista, pues te permite mayor adaptabilidad en el oído, quedándose bien fijados y ocasionando CERO molestia. Soy bastante quisquilloso con esto último, no tengo los oídos muy grandes y, a la mínima, el resto de auriculares se me hacen incómodos a la que los llevo puestos un par de horas seguidas. Pienso que las almohadillas tienen bastante que ver en todo esto último que he dicho, puede que simplemente haya sido suerte en mi caso y haya encontrado los auriculares ideales para mis oídos. En cualquier caso no podría estar más feliz con ellos.  Como único punto negativo, al menos que yo haya notado, es en lo referente a la cancelación de ruido activa, que si bien es cierto que con la última actualización ha mejorado bastante, sigue sin estar a la altura de los Jabra. Sin embargo se adaptan tan bien que ni siquiera me hace falta hacer uso de ella. Read more', 'These headphones are so well built with crystal clear sounds. The call quality and ANZ are also pretty impressive. Overall a great pick, and I am enjoying it :)', "Now the JBL Studio's are no longer available  the JBL Club Pro+ are the top of the range model, originally retailing for £200ish. For the current price of around £75, these are an absolute bargain. First things first  they are JBL's  pointing out the obvious  you don't buy JBL for flat acoustic sterility, JBL's offer up a bass forward, exciting sound. Bass is deep and controlled, mids rich and clear, highs are sharp and sweet without too much crash. You can tone it all down or up via the excellent app but that's missing the point. The app by the way has the most effective EQ of any I've tried so far. There are currently only 3 DJ profiles to choose from, which is slightly disappointing, plus the usual Bass, Jazz, Vocal etc settings. Control wise they are a little quirky, left bud can control the volume up and down OR noise cancelling. Right bud controls the track forward, back and pause. You can adjust the controls in the app but these aren't really suited to one ear only listening as you'll lose half the functions. The case is strong, easy to get the buds in and out, offers qi wireless charging and has little lights to show you have inserted the buds correctly. The only indication of case charge is a little red light though. More indication of case charge status would have been nice, but you can see this on the app. Battery life is good also. I've seen some reports that these are uncomfortable  I haven't found this at all  once adjusted via the app based 'fit check' function, these are on a par with most other twist lock buds  certainly more comfortable than Liberty pro's or Sony XM3's. I also have the JBL live pro + and prefer the club pro + as they seem to have more clarity of vocals. Noise cancelling  above average. I can't hear my wife or wind noise. These buds auto pause when taken out so I don't use the talk through function, there are 2 settings, talk thru which reduces the music to low volume and has a very natural sound for talking in shops etc, and Ambient Aware  this keeps the music volume similar but pipes through some external noises so you can be more aware of cars, kids etc. Overall these are an excellent set of buds, while they are on offer they are an absolute steal. In a blind test I'd put them up there with the Jabra 85t and Sennheiser momentums  but bear in mind I like the exciting dynamic sound these provide  Edited to add  all DJ profiles have been removed with the latest firmware upgrade. This is not even an option in the equalizer settings now. Shame as other brands (Soundcore) have quite a few to try out. It's as if JBL are phasing this model out for a newer version ? Read more"]

The case is solid and has a felt texture all around. Love the zipper on that thing. Smoooooth.  After owning for a week... The headphones have all the adjustability you'll need. The cups turn and fold inward for storage and transportation. The metal on the outside of the band makes for a great solid feel and adds a nice spring to it which makes it easy to take on and off. They don't squeeze too much like some tend to do. These have good bass output. Better than some of the more expensive headsets I've used. The noise cancelling function works superb. I feel sometimes like I am in a sound depravation chamber. It's eerie, in a good way. It's easy to adjust the noise cancellation if you want to listen to music but still hear others around you like in a work setting. The bluetooth links up easily and has a pleasant tone when connecting or disconnecting. The ear cups are nice and comfortable to wear.  Cons: I have a few things... but they are very minor. *The bluetooth will sometimes randomly disconnect but quickly reconnect. This is usually after like 45 min to an hour of listening... I don't have to intervene at all.... but is just annoying. *Like many ear cups... they use some kind of vinyl covering which does not breathe. All Reviews: ['As an Apple user, I wanted great over the ear headphones with noise cancellation, but there was Absolutely No Way I was going to drop the fat stacks on the Apple ones. I started looking around and considering my options, originally deciding on some SRhythm offbrand ones here on Amazon. When I came back with the money to buy, the SRhythms were sold out so it was back to browsing. At this point, I decided it would be a better idea to go with a trusted brand that didn’t have the possibility of disappearing from Amazon within the next few years.  The ideal headphone, for me, was the Sony XM5s  after reading reviews it sounded absolutely godly. But it also costs godly amounts of dollars, which was the original problem I was trying to avoid.  Enter JBL, I realized the speaker brand that went from “a few of your buddies ride or die by this brand” to a soundjunkie staple was IDEAL. I shopped around, looked at similar Skullcandy models, other brands similar in price but also not offering anything better than passive noise cancellation.  The comparable Skullcandy model (price wise, at least) has worse battery life, primarily because it uses (imo) a ridiculous number of microphones for Active Noise Cancellation. At the time of my purchase, the Skullcandy model also costed slightly more which made even less sense.  I find the noise cancellation on these to be easily comparable to the AirPod Pros I have used before. Especially with music playing, I cannot hear a single thing outside of my little bubble. I’ve used these at work for two days straight without ever having to plug them in. They connect to my phone with ease and the buttons on the side are very useful. The audio quality is crystal clear, and I often use these in the car instead of my stereo. These things perform beautifully.  The JBL app is also a stroke of genius, allowing me all the customizability that Apple tries to prevent me from having with any nonApple products. The different equalizer modes are absolutely killer too.  I only have two small gripes. For some reason, the lowest noise cancellation setting jacks up the outside microphone’s volume but completely mutes my music without pausing it. So I can hear if someone is talking to me, but there’s not even a hint of the song I was listening to. This is a little disappointing compared to the AirPods transparency mode.  The second one is that the ear cans on this thing are slightly too small for my ears, and I’m pretty sure I have relatively typical earsize (elementary school kids would have made sure I knew if I had some Dumbosized ears yanno!). Wearing the headphones for hours at a time makes the cartilage on the side and top of my ear sore, and if they had like a millimeter or two more diameter that could be fixed.  All in all, I consider these to be five star worthy because it’s an excellent value for the price. I absolutely love these things, and I hope they will last me a good while. I will be back to update my review on their durability after having owned them for longer. Read more', 'Fit is on the smaller side. I returned them because I didn’t find them comfortable', 'Me gustó la calidad de estos, son muy buenos a la hora de cancelar el sonido, incluyendo que también tiene un modo de transparencia y otro para hablar con alguien más, el micrófono me han dicho que es bueno, lo único malo que le encuentro es que si los quieres usar para un Xbox no vas a poder hablar por el micrófono aunque tenga el cable conectado, pero en si unos audífonos con una calidad de audio muy buena, unos bajos perfectos, y una conexión rápida a mi teléfono, además para mayor protección estos vinieron con una tela en la que los puedes guardar.', 'Très satisfait', 'Cumplen con su cometido, pero nada del otro mundo.']

Keine billige Verarbeitung oder Materialien, sondern einfach ... ja, sie fühlen sich toll an  anders kann ich das gar nicht beschreiben ;)  Die Ohrhörer gehören zu den kleinsten, die ich bislang getestet habe und fühlen sich, je nach Größe des Gehörgangs, etwas wackelig an. Allerdings sei gesagt, dass man so im Normalfall nicht den Kopf hin und her schüttelt, außer vielleicht auf einem HeavyMetalKonzert, aber da trägt man sowieso keine Kopfhörer :P Im Alltag fallen sie also nicht wirklich raus.  Das Wichtigtse: Der Klang überzeugt mich auf voller Linie! Der Ton ist klar, satt und hat einen guten Bass  nicht zu flach, nicht zu plump, nicht zu übertrieben  einfach ein schöner Klang! Da passen sowohl die Höhen als auch die Tiefen für mein Empfinden.  Das Koppeln funktioniert auch problemlos und was mich sehr positiv überrascht hat: ich kann es bei WhatsApp (Android 10) auch zum Telefonieren verwenden! Jedes andere BTHeadset im EarbudFormat klappte nämlich nicht (Gesprächspartner konnten mich nie hören, da es Probleme mit der Nutzung des Mikrofons gab  laut Internetrecherche ein bekanntes Problem von WhatsApp/Andorid). Multi point is better on Airpods atleast on Apple devices. I better not comment on ANC as I am not a fan of ANC as a feature itself(yes I am a rare species these days). Bass is definitely punchier than the Airpods. There are certain bass rumbles that give you goosebumps when using the Soundcore ones. 2. Sony WF1000XM4: These where very bad in volume on iPhone atleast. At 2.5X the price, the XM4s are definitely not a better pick than the Liberty NCs in any metric 3. Oppo Enco X2: Sound quality is comparable, but bass is definitely more punchy in the Liberty NCs. Other metrics can go either way. 4. Crossbeats Torq 1.0: Niche comparison, but these underrated beasts delivered very punchy bass compromising music quality. Liberty NCs have a little less punchy bass than the Torqs, but they make it up on the quality of bass and overall sound quality.  Bonus: Try the song “Pista the Run Anthem” on Youtube on the Liberty NCs after you do a HearID or by selecting Soundcore Signature or Bass Boost EQs. The absolute beginning of the track has a rumbly bit and you will be blown away. Read more", 'Se ajustan muy bien a mi oreja. Ya solo con eso aislan bastante del ruido exterior. Si a eso le sumas la cancelacion de sonido activa (yo los uso en modo adaptativo) el resultado es muy bueno. Los he testeado por la calle con trafico alto, en plazas concurridas, en la cocina con el extractor, y el resultado es muy adecuado. Vengo de unos Honor Magic Earbuds y los Soundcore le dan mil vueltas en cancelacion de sonido, en personalizacion de audio, en distancia, en duracion de la bateria, y en calidad de los micros. Tambien espero que sean mejores en durabilidad ya que los Honor, tras solo 2 anyos de uso, el bud izquierdo el ha perdido el 90% del volumen de sonido.  Los controles tactiles funcionan bien. La app que acompanya a los Soundcore es super completa. Puedes hacer hasta tests de estanqueidad de sonido y personalizar su sonido tras un test de audicion (HearID). En mi caso, me lo ha acertado bastante y solo he tenido que tocar el equalizador minimamente. Desde que lo compre han ido saliendo algunas actualizaciones de firmware, que he ido instalando sin problema.  La unica pega es que aun no entiendo muy bien lo del soporte multidispositivo, y me aparecen con dos nombres diferentes cuando hago una busqueda de dispositivos bluetooth a mi alrededor. A veces se queda conectado al que no quiero y tengo que resetear el bluetooth para conectar al otro. Quizas igual soy yo haciendo algo mal...  En cualquier caso estoy muy satisfecho con la compra y los recomendaria sin dudarlo por su buena calidad/precio (cuando los compre estaban a 71.99 euros) Read more', 'I had Liberty 3s for a year and a half but unfortunately lost them. These sound pretty much exactly the same (which is phenomenal) but are improved in almost every other way. The fit is much simpler and the silicon earbud tips work much better than they did on the 3s. One flaw that always annoyed me in the 3s was the additional rubber bumper you had to adjust to keep the bud in your ear. That had been fixed entirely with these. The 4s comfortable fit in my ear for long periods of time and will not fall out even when I’m sweating. Connectivity has been quick and easy for me so far and the soundcore app and settings have worked just fine and are simple and intuitive. Tap/touch controls feel maybe slightly more responsive than on the 3s, but the one drawback on the 4s is that the stem is a very small surface area to try to tap accurately. Sometimes you don’t tap the right spot, or sometimes you tap at an angle and the pad of your finger doesn’t touch where it needs to. It’s weird. Bit of a learning curve on that.  At this price, though, these earbuds are incredible and the best ones I’ve tried. I’m not willing to pay for the premium Sonys, Bose, or JBLs, but these are so good that I don’t even feel I’m missing out.']

All Reviews: ['منتج سيي للغاية ولا يوجد به عز للصوت', 'Unsurprisingly, Anker has done it again. These Bluetooth earbuds are absolutely incredible. Unlike other brands of earbuds I’ve tried, these things get loud; not loud to the point that you’ll hurt your ears or be unable to withstand it, but loud enough that you won’t be wishing you could turn them up more. The smart noise cancellation feature is really neat. I’m in construction so the noise levels vary greatly from day to day. The smart noise cancellation keeps up by changing the type of ANC. In addition, there’s an audible beep when you successfully tap for touch control which has absolutely zero delay. This is great to me because it confirms whether or not you actually touched the earbud. I posted a few side by side photos of these Soundcore P40i’s and one pair of my Soundcore Life P3’s because I wanted to know the size difference in the earbuds and the case and couldn’t find any reviews mentioning it or information elsewhere mentioning it. In case anyone is interested, the P40i’s case is a little bit smaller and the earbuds’ themselves are slightly shorter. It’s great because the P40i’s are EVEN MORE compact. The battery life of these is the best; bar none. 10h per earbud per charge. I have yet to hear the “battery low” alert. The addition of the phone stand clip within the case is ingenious and a new feature that I love. I watch lots of movies and tv shows on my phone. Now, rather than holding my phone, I can put it in the P40i’s case in front of me. It’s a small feature but works wonders for my use. Lastly, the sound quality of these earbuds is insane. All Reviews: ['RESUMO POSITIVO: MATERIAL BOM, BATERIA INSANA E CARREGAMENTO RÁPIDO RESUMO NEGATIVO: FALHAS DE CONEXÃO ESPORÁDICAS RARAS E CASE SEM TAMPA Comprei faz um mês, o aúdio é muito bom e o material também é muito bom, pois eu sou meio estabanado e já derrubei algumas vezes nesse tempo, tanto o case quanto o fone, e ele tá funcionando tranquilamente kkkk (perdi muitos fones assim ;;). Se eu tivesse que falar seu ponto mais forte é o tempo de duração da bateria, dura muito tempo e, quando colocado no case (com o case carregado) ele carrega em uns 10 minutos. O case fica laranja quando tá descarregando e vermelho quando está perto de descarregar. Então se você carregar o case de vez em quando, enquanto estiver usando o fone, e de vez quando deixar o fone carregar quando for conversar, ir tomar banho ou algo do tipo por uns 5/10 minutos, ele se torna imortal kkkk. Só descarregou COMIGO 1 vez, que eu usei o dia todo, da manhã até de tardezinha, sem carregar, então a bateria é impressionante. MAS NADA NESSA VIDA É PERFEITO, então têm dois pontos negativos. Primeiro, ele de vez em quando corta o som do nada. É raro, mas acontece kk. Segundo, e mais irritante na minha opnião, o case não tem tampa, e, consequentemente, é muito fácil entrar qualquer tipo de poeira onde os fones ficam, sujeira essa que é destacada pelo fato do fone ser branco kkkk. Então se você não quiser ser o porquinho do case imundo, tem que limpar regularmente, o que é bem chato. OBS: fazer exercícios físicos com ele é ruim devido a ele escorregar com movimentos bruscos ou quando você começa a suar. Então, caso você faça mais que uma musculação ou cardio de leve, ele não é um fone bom para você fazer exercícios físicos. OBS2: Fui no site da JBL oficial para checkar e tudo certo, registrei ele tranquilamente na minha conta. OBS3: Baixe o app da JBL para configurar ele e ter uma melhor experiência. RESUMINDO, acredito que, considerando a proposta de ser um fone de entrada de boa qualidade com um bom preço custobenéficio, ele inequivocadamente cumpre o que promete. 5 ESTRELAS Read more', "Dopo aver acquistato diverse altre cuffie mi sono deciso per queste JBL. E sono molto soddisfatto: si indossano perfettamente, la qualita' del suono e' ottima (tenuto conto del prezzo), il controllo via app e' un ulteriore plus. Vale il detto: chi piu' spende , meno spende. Forse costano un po' di piu' rispetto ad altri prodotti. Ma l'acquisto vale assolutamente la pena.", 'No tenía altas expectativas y se superaron con creces, los ajustes de oreja son geniales incluso para las que tenemos orejas pequeñas y la calidad de sonido muy buena, también se escucha muy bien la voz en las llamadas, buen micrófono :D', 'السماعة من دون غطاء نفس العلبة', ' Ich habe diese Kopfhörer und die Soundcore Ai3 bestellt. Ich habe eine lange Rezension bei den Soundcore geschrieben und beide verglichen, das werde ich diesmal nicht tun, aber ich werde euch meine ehrliche Meinung geben was ich von den JBL Wave Buds halte. Sind gut verpackt angekommen, soweit sogut. Einmal ausgepackt, gleich gesehen das es eine App dazu gibt, diese gedownloadet und die Einstellung und der Rest funktionierten sehr intuitiv, man kann nicht viel falsch machen. Die + = Erstmal zu der Soundqualität, ich war echt positiv überrascht, habe für dieses Geld nicht sooooo viel erwartet. Es gibt in der App auch einen Equalizer, also kann man wenn einem etwas nicht passt, sich etwas rumspielen und vielleicht genau den Ton erreichen denn man sich wünscht, für mich war es einfach, BASS!!! Für mich ist immer der Bass wichtig, und wow ich wurde nicht enttäuscht! Außer ich höre mir ein Hörbuch an, dann switche ich um, dauert keine 5Sekunden! Also an der Soundqualität kann man echt nichts aussetzen, ich bin sogar der Meinung das es mit den ganz Großen(Marken) mithalten kann, mein Bruder hat alle Apfelprodukte(na gut ich habe auch ein IPhone und ein Mac Book, das war’s dann aber auch) aufjedenfall hat er die AirPods , sowie Sennheiser Kopfhörer, ich habe mal den Test gemacht und drei Songs aus drei verschiedenen Genres ausgesucht und mir die Songs auf jedem Gerät angehört. Also bei den Äpfeln muss ich echt sagen, das ist reinste Abzocke, da hörten sich meine JBl besser an. Bei den Sennheiser muss ich zugeben das sie um einen Tick doch besser waren, aber wisst ihr wieviel die gekostet haben?260€!!!! Und für das Geld hat es mich jetzt nicht von den Socken gehaut. Mein Bruder hat den gleichen Test gemacht und bei den Apple war er sofort, ja man merkt echt kaum einen Unterschied bei den Sennheiser wurde er aber echt sensibel, weil ich weiß wie sehr er sie liebt und wieviel sie gekostet haben, wenn mir jemand mit 53€ Kopfhörern kommt und sagt lass uns mal testen und dir wird klar, das es nicht das Geld wert ist. Zu seiner Verteidigung sie sind besser. Der Sound ist klarer, sättigender und der Bass kann echt was, aber das sind so kleine Nuancen, das man sich fragen muss, war es das Geld wert?! Ok zum nächsten Punkt + sobald man die Kopfhörer rausnimmt aus dem Case verbinden sie sich mit meinem Handy, ich liebes es, bei meinen letzten musste ich manchmal echt manuell reingehen und sie verbinden, wie nervig ist das denn? Ich habe einige Rezensionen gelesen das sie keinen Meter sich entfernen dürfen sonst bricht die Verbindung ab. Vielleicht hatten sie ein Montagsprodukt? Oder ich weiß nicht, aber ich lasse mein Handy oft im Wohnzimmer und gehe den Flur entlang bis ganz zum Schluss wo an der linken Seite die Küche ist, da sind also mehr als eine dicke Mauer zwischen mir und meinem Handy und nicht einmal hatte ich Probleme mit der Verbindung oder dergleichen. Ich behaupte nicht das diese Leute lügen, aber ich beschreibe einfach meine Erfahrung und ich hatte jetzt genügend Zeit es zu testen. Und einmal wollte ich den Müll runterbringen, habe aber vergessen das ich die Kopfhörer drin hatte, erst im 3oder 2 Stock(ich wohne im 5.ten) brach die Verbindung dann ab. Also auch diesbezüglich für mich ein absolutes PLUS! Weiteres + das Produkt wirbt damit kein Noice Cancelling zu haben, DAS STIMMT NICHT!!!!! Ich habe zwei Fotos hochgeladen von der App und da sieht man wo draufsteht „Umgebungsgeräuschkontrolle“ wenn man auf das Ambient Aware drauf ist, hört man die Musik aber man hört auch alles andere und noch stärker ist es wenn man das „Talk Thru“ verwendet, man kann ein Gespräch mit jemanden führen und leise im Hintergrund hört man leise noch die Musik. Ich war vollkommen überrascht, auf der Seite wird ganz und klar damit geworben das sie KEIN Noice Cancelling haben, und trotzdem sitz ich nun hier und bin der lebende Beweis das es sehr wohl funktioniert und das Beste kommt jetzt, die anderen Kopfhörer, die Soundcore Ai3 die damit werben Noice Cancelling zu haben, ich habe es immer wieder getestet unter verschiedenen Bedingungen und ich muss sagen DIESE KOPFHÖRER(Soundcore) haben MEINER MEINUNG nach kein Noice Cancelling, also wenn ich mich auf die App von Soundcore verlassen würde, und nicht meinen Kopf eingeschaltet hätte, wäre ich abermals und abermals überfahren worden, noch habe ich meinen Freund nach mir schreien gehört. Also ganz, ganz übel. Ich finde es fast fahrlässig zu behaupten das dein Gerät etwas kann, was es offensichtlich nicht kann.(das war aber der einzige minus Punkt bei den Soundcore,sonst sind sie auch echt gute Kopfhörer) Dementsprechend war ich echt happy als ich begriffen habe das ich jetzt sogar „Noice Cancelling“ habe aber noch viel mehr das „Talk thru „ dadurch kann ich endlich wenn mich jemand auf der Straße anspricht nicht gleich meine Kopfhörer rausnehmen müssen sondern kann das schnell einschalten und kann ein normales Gespräch führen. Nächster Punkt + die Langlebigkeit des Akkus 32h werden versprochen und ich kann es jetzt nicht zu 100% bestätigen, ich habe nicht jede Stunde gezählt, aber sie halten wirklich lange. Als sie ankamen waren sie bei der Hälfte ich war so ungeduldig das ich sie gleich im FullModus austesten wollte und benutzen wollte das ich sie nicht mal auf 100% aufgeladen habe und trotzdem haben sie echt lange gehalten. Ich meine wenn ich bedenke wie oft und für wie lange ich sie Tag ein und Tag aus benutzt habe, Wow, was ich auch echt cool finde ist das wenn du in die App gehst(sieht man auf dem Foto das ich hochgeladen habe) genau siehst wieviel % dein linker und wieviel dein rechter haben. Vorne auf dem case gibt es auch drei „Lichter“ und diese zeigen dir grob an wie lange du noch hast, aber mit der App siehst du sowieso auf den Prozent genau wie lange du noch hast. Auch das fand ich cool gemacht(die App) + Anrufe: Ich habe es mehrmals mit meiner mum, mit meinem Bruder und Freundinnen getestet, man kann super mit denen telefonieren, das gegenüber versteht einen vollkommen klar, also auch hier wurde ich positiv überrascht weil ich Rezensionen gelesen habe wo angeblich die Person die andere überhaupt nicht verstehen konnte…Ich will ja niemanden etwas unterstellen, aber bei mir hat es super geklappt und ich verwende es fast täglich, wenn ich unterwegs bin und meine mum mich anruft, wir quatschten dann meistens für eine halbe Stunde und nicht ein einziges Mal hat sie gesagt ich verstehe dich nicht, oder ich verstehe dich schlechter, sie meinte sie merkte garnicht ob ich mit Kopfhörern oder mit dem Iphone selbst telefonierte. + Das ist nun ein Plus für mich für wenn anderen kann es ein minus sein….der Tragekomfort der Kopfhörer, ich muss aber zugeben das ich bis jetzt nie Probleme hatte mit keinem Modell von Kopfhörern, meine Ohren scheinen wohl sehr Kopfhörerfreundlich zu sein :D Nein Spaß bei Seite, ich musste mich auch erstmal austesten( mit in der Packung sind auch drei Noppen in drei verschiedenen Größen, für mich waren es dann die kleinsten, sind die Kopfhörer mal drinnen, ist es als hätte ich nichts in meinen Ohren, wirklich! Im Gegensatz zu den Soundcore, anfangs waren sie cool, aber nach einigen Stunden Benutzung fingen sie an wehzutun, aber ich bin mir sicher das liegt an mir weil ich sie falsch drinnen hatte! Aber trotzdem wenn ich die Soundcore drinnen habe, merke ich das ich Kopfhörer drinnen habe, sie haben nicht so einen Tragekomfort wie die Wave Buds. Ich kann laufen, springen, sagen wir mal so, sie halten mein Intervalltraining in der Früh aus und das sagt viel aus! Sie halten und verrutschen nicht mal um einen Millimeter!  So und jetzt kommt der RIESEN GROẞE MINUS PUNKT!  😱 Das Case ist offen, omg wie schlimm, mir fiel aber echt nichts anderes ein was mir negativ aufgefallen wäre, aber selbst das Problem mit dem Case lässt sich mit 8€ klären, kauft auf Amazon aus Silikon gemachte Schutzhüllen für die Cases! O XB900N faz um trabalho competente nesse quesito, bloqueando sons constantes como barulhos de chuva, ventiladores, etc, porém é quase nulo com vozes, para conseguir isso só com o WH1000XM4 pagando quase o dobro aqui no Brasil. Quanto aos formatos de áudio suportados ele é bem completo, SBC, AAC, aptX, aptX HD, LDAC, o que permite o streaming de áudio de alta resolução em conexões Bluetooth. A qualidade de áudio é surpreendente, sendo possível ouvir uma boa separação dos instrumentos e das vozes, tudo isso com graves excelentes. Se você não quiser tantos graves é possível ajustar a equalização pelo aplicativo Sony | Headphones Connect. Também oferece suporte ao 360 Reality Audio, mas sinceramente não acho que seja um fator de decisão, pois além de não ter suporte ao Spotify, ter um número bem limitado de músicas disponíveis, cerca de 1000 até o momento, é algo que você provavelmente vai usar durante o período de testes de algum aplicativo e depois nunca mais. Vale ressaltar que na caixa vem um cupom para você utilizar no Deezer, Tidal ou nugs.net, que oferece um período de testes grátis. A qualidade de construção é sim superior aos fones de entrada da marca, mas poderia ser melhor, especialmente no plástico utilizado no seu corpo. Já as almofadas de couro são extremamente confortáveis e o arco superior acolchoado ajudam no conforto. No geral é um produto sólido e que passa uma sensação de produto premium. Os pontos negativos são o tempo de carregamento que é de aproximadamente 7 horas, Bluetooth 4.2 e ele não vem com uma case e sim com uma bolsa de tecido. É uma ótima opção para quem não quer, ou não pode, gastar tanto no XM4, ou até mesmo num Airpods Max, mas que ainda sim queira usufruir do cancelamento de ruído e de um áudio de alta qualidade. Read more', 'Soy amante de la música, de todos los géneros, habitualmente usaba unos Bose Soundtrue, muy buenos pero no son inalambricos, y pues honestamente tenía la idea de que duraban poco las baterías, y el sonido disminuiría en su calidad, pues bien con sos audífonos sony son una chulada, suenan hermoso, el jazz es muy suave, le música clásica mantiene los agudos y frecuencias bajas de los instrumentos de viento, el metal suenan geniales los bajos, y la electrónica jamás se había escuchado tan clara, los utilizo con un sony walkman DAC y vaya que exprime todo el potencial de estos audífonos. Los uso todo el día en mis traslados del trabajo, en mis caminatas, o simplemente para relajarme, la batería les dura una semana, apagados sin bluetooth casi un mes (Si también los puedes usar apagados con el cable 3.5 incluido) Las esponjas son bastante cómodas y suaves, no se cansa uno, la cancelación de ruido no es la mejor, sin embargo por el costo es bastante buena. También es algo triste que no vengan con estuche, solo con una bolsa, yo siempre los cargo en el cuello, al no utilizarlo pero se pueden dañar las esponjas por lo cual recomiendo conseguir un estuche básico barato. De todo lo demás son una maravilla, y bueno yo los conseguí en una buena oferta casi a la mitad del costo actual.', "SOUND QUALITY AND BASS, I own a pair of Sony 1000XM3 and QC35, these definitely have more bass. They definitely don't sound as clear as either of the two, but they still sound great. They are less “flat” sounding and more lively and fun. If you want your ears to vibrate like the Skullcady Crushers, set the equalizer to Exited and set the headphones to Arena mode, then crank up the volume, while nowhere near as much vibration as the skullcandys, its there if you’re into that.  NOISE CANCELLING, I would say these headphones cancel about 60%70% of the noise that the Bose QC35s and XM3s/Bose 700s cancel out (which is really good). I would definitely place these in the top 10 noise cancelling headphones out there. However if you only want noise cancelling then you might want to look into the Sony 1000XM3 or Bose 700. With the XB900N you will still be able to hear some outside noise such as loud fans, chatter, etc at low volumes (40% or so) if you want to block out noise fully it is possible but you will have to crank them up to 7080% volume.  I listen to them at about 40% volume and its loud enough for me, while other headphones i have to set them near 80% volume.  BLUETOOTH AND APP, these are very easy to connect to your devices, hold the power button for 7 seconds then they go into pairing mode, then just connect to them using your device...no hastle. The app also works flawlessly and let me tell you this app is no joke!   You can change the noise cancelling level (20 levels).   You can set between amazon alexa or google assistant   You can change the sound to come from front, front left/right, or rear left/right.   The have an equalizer which lets you adjust bass, mids, highs, etc. It also comes with some presets if you want to just boost bass, vocals, trebble etc. This equalizer really changes the way these headphones sound, this aint no gimmick!   Surround VPT, I don’t know why this feature is not that popular but when you change it creates a feeling of surround sound, the settings are Arena, Concert Hall, Outdoor Stage, and Club.  When you set the headphones to arena mode and you watch a movie it literally sounds like you have two soundbars in your ears, its insane that a simple setting on an app can make such a difference... these things sound like a movie theatre!  I have owned many pair of headphones, and you get what you pay for. I would definitely say these are worth the $250 price tag.  In a nutshell...  Those who want a good pair of headphones and want to save $100 buy the XB900Ns.  If you want basically double the noise cancelling, and a cleaner sound (less bass) get the Sony XM3s.  Can’t go wrong with either, both are great. Read more", "Sound quality is simply amazing. Bass is punchy and feels great. Very comfortable to wear. Comfortable cushioning as well. Bass boost and sound quality is good if you select “stereo” over “hands free” option on PC. Which means sound is better with headphones on than off.']
